body:
## 🚀 Feature Proposal

Add `Symbol.iterator` methods to classes that currently implement callback-based `*each*` methods:

* `Row#eachCell`
* `Column#eachCell`
* `Worksheet#eachRow` (and possibly an additional iterator method for `Worksheet#eachColumnKey`)
* `CellMatrix#forEach`
* `DefinedNames#forEach`
* `Workbook#eachSheet`

## Motivation

Currently, these are all implemented via callbacks, which are less than ideal due to lack of async support and inability to break early without `throw`ing.

To avoid redundancy while supporting backward compatibility, the existing methods could be provided as wrappers around the iterator methods.

## Example

Usage:

```ts
for (const cell of sheet.getRow(1)) {
    console.log(cell.value)
}
```

Code changes could look something like this (example for `Row#eachCell`, passes all existing tests):

<details>
<summary>Diff</summary>

```diff
diff --git a/exceljs.d.ts b/exceljs.d.ts
index 5eb691e..6d2ee66 100644
--- a/exceljs.d.ts
+++ b/exceljs.d.ts
@@ -585,6 +585,12 @@ export interface Row extends Style {
 	 */
 	eachCell(opt: { includeEmpty: boolean }, callback: (cell: Cell, colNumber: number) => void): void;
 
+	/**
+	 * Iterate over all cells in a row.
+	 * @param opt.includeEmpty - if true, include empty cells
+	 */
+	[Symbol.iterator](opt?: { includeEmpty: boolean }): Generator<Cell>;
+
 	/**
 	 * Cut one or more cells (cells to the right are shifted left)
 	 *
diff --git a/lib/doc/row.js b/lib/doc/row.js
index 054f52a..c891370 100644
--- a/lib/doc/row.js
+++ b/lib/doc/row.js
@@ -126,23 +126,29 @@ class Row {
     }
   }
 
+  *[Symbol.iterator](options) {
+    if (options && options.includeEmpty) {
+      for (const i of this._cells.keys()) {
+        yield this.getCell(i + 1);
+      }
+    } else {
+      for (const i of Object.keys(this._cells)) {
+        const cell = this._cells[i];
+        if (cell && cell.type !== Enums.ValueType.Null) {
+          yield cell;
+        }
+      }
+    }
+  }
+
   // Iterate over all non-null cells in this row
   eachCell(options, iteratee) {
     if (!iteratee) {
       iteratee = options;
       options = null;
     }
-    if (options && options.includeEmpty) {
-      const n = this._cells.length;
-      for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
-        iteratee(this.getCell(i), i);
-      }
-    } else {
-      this._cells.forEach((cell, index) => {
-        if (cell && cell.type !== Enums.ValueType.Null) {
-          iteratee(cell, index + 1);
-        }
-      });
+    for (const cell of this[Symbol.iterator](options)) {
+      iteratee(cell, Number(cell.col));
     }
   }
```

</details>
